<quantity box="[1109,1189,249,274]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
high, no coppiniae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,285,310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description.</emphasis>
Stems up to 
<quantity box="[501,583,285,310]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
high, almost completely polysiphonic, and divided into internodes with a distinct zigzag arrangement. Some anastomoses between branches present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Hydrothecae alternately arranged in approximately one plane. Hydrotheca (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1191,357,382]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[266,1353,236,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1380,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acryptolaria crassicaulis (Allman, 1888): A, hydrotheca; B, macrobasic mastigophore nematocyst (arrow). Cryptolarella abyssicola (Allman, 1888): C-D, hydrothecae; E, gonotheca. Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): F, hydrotheca; G, detail of basal part of hydrotheca; H, isorhiza nematocyst. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-F), 100 µm (G), 10 µm (B, H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) tubular, but curved outwards, particularly at distal part. Diameter roughly constant in free part, but gradually decreasing towards basal part. Free part of adcauline wall distinctly convex; adnate one only slightly convex. Abcauline wall concave at distal third, straight basally. Hydrothecal aperture circular, rim even, sometimes with renovations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Measurements (in µm). 
<emphasis box="[479,610,501,526]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hydrotheca</emphasis>
: diameter at aperture 250–260; length of free adcauline wall 300–470. 
<emphasis box="[151,252,537,562]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cnidome</emphasis>
: macrobasic mastigophores (
<figureCitation box="[580,667,537,562]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[266,1353,236,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1380,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acryptolaria crassicaulis (Allman, 1888): A, hydrotheca; B, macrobasic mastigophore nematocyst (arrow). Cryptolarella abyssicola (Allman, 1888): C-D, hydrothecae; E, gonotheca. Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): F, hydrotheca; G, detail of basal part of hydrotheca; H, isorhiza nematocyst. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-F), 100 µm (G), 10 µm (B, H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), 15.5–17.5 x 5.5–6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" box="[199,1298,573,598]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,573,598]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
The material from JC037/019 has slightly larger hydrothecae than previously recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This constitutes the third confirmed record of the species. See 
<bibRefCitation box="[893,1186,609,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L., Marques, A. &amp; Migotto, A. E. (2007) Revision of the genus Acryptolaria Norman, 1875 (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Lafoeidae). Journal of Natural History, 41, 229 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930701228132" type="journal article">
Peña Cantero 
<emphasis box="[1049,1105,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
for a re-description of the 
<typeStatus box="[192,240,646,670]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
material and a discussion of its relationship with other species in the genus. The material examined agrees with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Allman" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[210,378,681,706]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Lafoeidae" genus="Acryptolaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="crassicaulis">
<emphasis box="[210,378,681,706]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. crassicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape and size of the hydrotheca, the size of the nematocysts and the marked zigzag arrangement of the internodes. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Allman 1877)" authorityName="Allman" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Allman" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[504,923,717,742]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Lafoeidae" genus="Acryptolaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis box="[504,748,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Acryptolaria conferta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Allman" box="[764,915,717,742]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Allman, G. J. (1877) Report on the Hydroida collected during the exploration of the Gulf Stream by L. F. de Pourtales, assistant United States Coast Survey. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 5 (2), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1877">Allman 1877</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
also has a marked zigzag arrangement of the internodes and a similar hydrotheca, but the nematocysts are distinctly larger and the hydrothecae are smaller.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,504,789,814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
This is a deep-water species, found at depths from 236 (
<bibRefCitation author="Pena" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2010) Species of Acryptolaria Norman, 1875 (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Lafoeidae) collected in the Western Pacific by various French expeditions, with the description of nineteen new species. Zoosystema, 32, 267 - 332. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2010 n 2 a 5" type="journal article" year="2010">Peña Cantero &amp; Vervoort 2010</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<quantity box="[256,330,825,850]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.56" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="756.0">756 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Allman" box="[346,501,825,850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Allman, G. J. (1888) Report on the Hydroida dredged by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Part II. The Tubularinae, Corymorphinae, Campanularinae, Sertularinae, and Thalamophora. Report of the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger 1873 - 1876, 23, 1 - 90." type="journal article" year="1888">Allman 1888</bibRefCitation>
). Present material ranges from 
<quantity box="[861,1046,825,850]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.377" metricValueMax="2.754" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2377.0" valueMax="2754.0" valueMin="2000.0">
<date box="[861,1013,825,850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2000" valueMax="2754">2000 to 2754</date>
m
</quantity>
, considerably increasing its lower bathymetric limit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,249,1030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The species has an uncertain distribution. It is recorded with certainty off 
<collectingRegion box="[1071,1188,897,922]" country="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" name="Ascension" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<collectingCountry box="[1071,1188,897,922]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ascension</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
Island (
<geoCoordinate box="[1287,1431,897,922]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" precision="15" value="7.9055557">07°54’20’’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,301,934,958]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" precision="15" value="-14.472221">14°28’20’’W</geoCoordinate>
), and in waters of the 
<collectingRegion box="[570,747,933,958]" country="New Caledonia" name="Province des Iles" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Loyalty Islands</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[808,986,933,958]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pena" box="[1003,1371,934,958]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2010) Species of Acryptolaria Norman, 1875 (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Lafoeidae) collected in the Western Pacific by various French expeditions, with the description of nineteen new species. Zoosystema, 32, 267 - 332. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2010 n 2 a 5" type="journal article" year="2010">Peña Cantero &amp; Vervoort 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The present material, which constitutes the third confirmed record of the species, comes from Rockall Trough and the Mid-Atlantic Ridge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
